1
00:00:04,115 --> 00:00:30,897
so we can start the standing meditation it takes about 10 to 15 minutes and if that's too long for you we'll just sit down so standing make sure you feel grounded balanced lifting up through the spine to the top of the head

2
00:00:33,697 --> 00:00:34,798
Standing tall.

3
00:00:40,023 --> 00:00:42,204
Spend a moment now relaxing.

4
00:00:44,866 --> 00:00:45,468
The brow.

5
00:00:45,508 --> 00:00:53,854
Eyes looking downward, unfocused.

6
00:00:59,401 --> 00:00:59,960
The jaw.

7
00:01:00,841 --> 00:01:02,082
Is there any tension there?

8
00:01:04,561 --> 00:01:08,629
If so, just waggle it about a bit or clench the jaw and relax.

9
00:01:14,501 --> 00:01:15,121
Shoulders.

10
00:01:18,447 --> 00:01:19,370
Any tension there?

11
00:01:21,153 --> 00:01:22,856
If so, give them a good squeeze.

12
00:01:31,492 --> 00:01:51,746
hands joined in front or by the side whatever's comfortable so just acknowledge the posture energy running up the spine to the top of the head everything else just hanging off relax

13
00:01:59,337 --> 00:02:01,641
Draw your attention now to the soles of your feet.

14
00:02:02,061 --> 00:02:03,284
What can you feel down there?

15
00:02:08,331 --> 00:02:11,598
Can you isolate the sensations of pressure?

16
00:02:20,212 --> 00:02:24,400
Can you isolate the sensations of warmth or coolness?

17
00:02:32,901 --> 00:02:36,526
What about the more subtle sensations that tell you what you're standing on?

18
00:02:37,067 --> 00:02:40,050
The sponginess of carpets, the hardness of wood?

19
00:02:53,304 --> 00:02:57,829
Can you isolate areas of the souls where the sensations are neutral?

20
00:03:01,014 --> 00:03:05,502
Can you get in contact with those around the instep maybe?

21
00:03:16,277 --> 00:03:24,068
Becoming aware of how the sensations are continuously changing as the body rebalances itself.

22
00:03:24,088 --> 00:03:26,111
The body rebalances itself.

23
00:03:33,770 --> 00:03:38,197
And just acknowledge that these sensations arise whether we want them to or not.

24
00:03:38,717 --> 00:03:41,281
They're not under our direct control.

25
00:03:53,459 --> 00:03:54,461
So let's take our time.

26
00:03:54,760 --> 00:04:00,569
Let's come up the body, see what we can feel both on the surface and the inside of the body.

27
00:04:01,681 --> 00:04:05,784
And be aware of areas that seem to be devoid of feeling, just empty.

28
00:04:27,718 --> 00:04:31,932
When you get to the abdomen, can you feel the sensations caused by the breath there?

29
00:04:33,336 --> 00:04:34,641
The rise and fall?

30
00:04:40,238 --> 00:04:41,221
Is there any tension?

31
00:04:55,985 --> 00:04:59,790
coming up into the stomach area can you feel the breath there?

32
00:05:01,192 --> 00:05:02,072
is it more prominent?

33
00:05:09,101 --> 00:05:22,499
is there any tension there?

34
00:05:22,519 --> 00:05:24,321
moving up into the chest

35
00:05:25,971 --> 00:05:27,112
Can you feel the breath there?

36
00:05:30,476 --> 00:05:31,437
Is that more prominent?

37
00:05:32,459 --> 00:05:33,661
Do you have a shallow breath?

38
00:05:40,709 --> 00:05:41,490
Any tensions?

39
00:05:53,963 --> 00:05:54,865
Feel the heartbeat?

40
00:06:08,327 --> 00:06:09,689
Shoulders still relaxed.

41
00:06:17,341 --> 00:06:17,862
The jaw.

42
00:06:25,091 --> 00:06:25,673
The brow.

43
00:06:25,713 --> 00:06:36,588
When you get to the scalp, scan it like you did the soles of your feet.

44
00:06:36,928 --> 00:06:38,031
What can you feel up there?

45
00:06:53,923 --> 00:06:58,690
Now, without moving your eyes, just become aware of the colours and shapes ahead of you.

46
00:07:13,694 --> 00:07:14,615
Any sounds?

47
00:07:21,581 --> 00:07:28,894
If you're in a quiet room, it might just be the sound of the electrical equipment in your body humming in your ears.

48
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:47,185
What's the atmosphere of the room you're in like?

49
00:07:57,728 --> 00:08:01,076
Can you sense the presence of those around you or near you?

50
00:08:09,797 --> 00:08:12,041
So your attention is completely out there.

51
00:08:27,901 --> 00:08:35,190
Now at the same time, bring in the in here, the feet, the breath, sensations in the body, both inside and outside.

52
00:08:43,139 --> 00:08:45,623
This is the bubble of our consciousness.

53
00:08:47,446 --> 00:08:54,735
This is the world we are actually experiencing moment after moment, being created by this complex organism.

54
00:08:56,486 --> 00:08:58,909
We can't get outside it, underneath it, above it.

55
00:08:58,929 --> 00:09:00,351
This is it.

56
00:09:01,813 --> 00:09:03,917
This is the world as we experience it.

57
00:09:04,356 --> 00:09:06,019
This is our universe.

58
00:09:07,280 --> 00:09:08,982
And we're always at the centre of it.

59
00:09:15,951 --> 00:09:17,094
So we may as well relax.

60
00:09:18,855 --> 00:09:22,139
Relax into this present moment, wide awake.

61
00:09:24,027 --> 00:09:27,500
And just allow the attention to move to whatever draws it.

62
00:09:28,222 --> 00:09:31,918
Something you see, now something you hear, now something you feel.

63
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:35,049
Just hang loose within that globe.

64
00:10:13,623 --> 00:10:14,384
Relaxing.

65
00:10:15,666 --> 00:10:18,369
Abiding in the present moment, wide awake.

66
00:10:21,393 --> 00:10:25,238
In this mode, just being, we can let go of ideas of achieving something.

67
00:10:25,658 --> 00:10:26,419
That's doing.

68
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:29,663
Doing something now for some future result.

69
00:10:30,325 --> 00:10:34,429
But here, in this mode, just being, this is the result.

70
00:10:34,811 --> 00:10:36,253
There's no reason for being.

71
00:10:36,293 --> 00:10:38,735
It just is.

72
00:11:15,418 --> 00:11:16,139
Relaxing.

73
00:11:17,381 --> 00:11:20,525
Dwelling in the present moment, wide awake.

74
00:11:22,328 --> 00:11:27,015
In this mode, just being, there's only this ever-presenting moment.

75
00:11:27,296 --> 00:11:28,837
There's no past, there's no future.

76
00:11:29,359 --> 00:11:31,702
Just this moment, here and now.

77
00:11:33,264 --> 00:11:36,649
So there's no reason to plan, even looking forward to anything.

78
00:11:38,131 --> 00:11:38,893
It doesn't matter.

79
00:11:40,355 --> 00:11:41,456
We're not going anywhere.

80
00:11:43,058 --> 00:11:43,840
In this mode,

81
00:11:44,917 --> 00:11:46,337
We're always arriving.

82
00:12:22,986 --> 00:12:23,748
Relaxing.

83
00:12:24,928 --> 00:12:27,932
Inhabiting the present moment, wide awake.

84
00:12:29,715 --> 00:12:32,378
In this mode, we're sitting back within ourselves.

85
00:12:32,938 --> 00:12:34,821
We're not reacting, not responding.

86
00:12:35,542 --> 00:12:38,524
Just watching, feeling, experiencing.

87
00:12:39,986 --> 00:12:42,971
And the world is just arising and passing away.

88
00:12:44,513 --> 00:12:50,799
Because we're not engaged, we don't have to present some body, be a person, a personality.

89
00:12:52,230 --> 00:12:53,668
We can be anonymous.

90
00:13:21,796 --> 00:13:32,265
relaxing, abiding in the present moment, wide awake, achieving nothing, going nowhere, being nobody.

91
00:13:35,610 --> 00:13:40,234
In this mode, we're developing five of the seven factors that lead to liberation.

92
00:13:41,495 --> 00:13:48,241
There's the awareness, of course, and there is that steadiness of attention, a phrase I prefer,

93
00:13:49,370 --> 00:13:52,273
concentration which I think makes us feel tight.

94
00:13:53,715 --> 00:13:57,860
It's just the effort needed to maintain steadiness of attention.

95
00:14:01,283 --> 00:14:11,394
A sense of calmness in that steadiness, even if the body feels restless and the heart agitated, the watcher, the observer is calm.

96
00:14:13,788 --> 00:14:15,950
And then there's the quality of equanimity.

97
00:14:16,730 --> 00:14:22,157
The dictionary says this is a balanced mind, but it should be a balanced mind and heart.

98
00:14:23,479 --> 00:14:28,504
Just letting go of holding on to views and opinions, be completely open-minded.

99
00:14:28,543 --> 00:14:37,933
And the heart, to let go of its prejudices, its fears, its aversions, its preferences, open-hearted.

100
00:14:37,974 --> 00:14:42,259
Open-hearted and open-minded.

101
00:14:45,985 --> 00:14:54,057
When these are established, we can bring in that curiosity, specifically around the three characteristics of existence.

102
00:14:54,077 --> 00:14:58,565
Impermanence, how we create suffering, and not self.

103
00:14:59,807 --> 00:15:00,828
So this is the base.

104
00:15:01,629 --> 00:15:05,056
You can always return to it in sitting and in daily life.

105
00:15:07,659 --> 00:15:13,308
And in daily life, to maintain this poise stops us from being carried away by emotions.

106
00:15:14,791 --> 00:15:25,082
You've had a phone call, you've finished a piece of work, you've been out and about, and you feel anxious, irritated, overexcited.

107
00:15:25,482 --> 00:15:39,099
But if you can just stop after every action, after every piece of work, after every conversation, and let the heart empty itself, then in the clarity and calmness, you can see the next intention.

108
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:44,325
We can decide whether it's wholesome or skillful or otherwise.

109
00:15:46,549 --> 00:15:54,660
If it is unwholesome and unskillful, we just stay still with that energy until it dies away, or at least begins to die away.

110
00:15:55,961 --> 00:15:57,845
And so it doesn't have such a hold on us.

111
00:15:58,905 --> 00:16:00,908
If it's skillful, of course, we empower it.

112
00:16:02,730 --> 00:16:08,619
Just in this very simple way, we can better our habits and improve our personalities.

113
00:16:09,659 --> 00:16:11,663
But it takes this degree of attention.

114
00:16:16,029 --> 00:16:18,212
Our next intention is to sit.

115
00:16:20,135 --> 00:16:31,951
So let us now begin to practice in the way the Mahasi Sayadaw would have us by slowing everything down and becoming aware of the tiniest movements.

116
00:16:31,971 --> 00:16:43,287
We can begin to use noting words to keep the attention tethered to the object and stop it wandering off into fantasies, moving, stretching, lifting, placing, lowering.

117
00:16:45,089 --> 00:16:54,423
taking our time, aware of all the movements it takes to get this body into a sitting posture, intending to sit.

118
00:17:56,182 --> 00:18:24,451
make sure the posture is the expression of the awakened one like a good statue lift up from the lower abdomen the muscles in the lower back when you do this you will feel the breath in the abdomen much more clearly and then lift up the spine to the top of the head spend the initial moments relaxing the brow

119
00:18:28,803 --> 00:18:51,721
eyes gently closed, the jaw, shoulders, and hands on your lap, whatever feels comfortable.

120
00:18:58,250 --> 00:19:07,902
acknowledging the posture, energized up the spine, everything else relaxed.

121
00:19:07,922 --> 00:19:15,971
If in our sitting the body begins to slump, just make the intention, intending to lift, lifting, lifting.

122
00:19:16,952 --> 00:19:24,342
If the body becomes tense, intending to relax, relaxing, relaxing.

123
00:19:34,817 --> 00:19:40,864
Draw the attention now to the breath of the abdomen, or wherever you feel it most, using a noting word.

124
00:19:42,045 --> 00:19:46,648
Rising, rising, falling, falling.

125
00:19:48,932 --> 00:19:55,157
If you're established at the nostrils and don't want to move to the abdomen, in, in, out, out.

126
00:19:57,680 --> 00:19:59,922
Get in touch with the breath, the feel of it.

127
00:20:01,344 --> 00:20:04,707
Just relax the attention onto those feelings.

128
00:22:49,842 --> 00:22:56,311
If the mind is wandering, when you wake up out of it, really recognize and acknowledge what it's doing.

129
00:22:57,233 --> 00:23:00,398
Worrying, worrying, planning, planning.

130
00:23:02,321 --> 00:23:07,750
And draw the attention away and bring it back to the breath and determine to stay there.

131
00:23:11,105 --> 00:23:21,897
Feeling sleepy or tired, just lift the spine, open the eyes just a little, and if the sleepiness is still there, you can open them wide, but keep the attention inward.

132
00:23:26,223 --> 00:23:36,977
Just relaxing the attention on the sensations caused by the breath, allowing those neutral sensations to bring silence to the mind,

133
00:23:37,446 --> 00:23:41,871
Calmness to the heart, stillness to the body.

134
00:26:28,288 --> 00:26:35,057
If the mind is wandering, when you wake up out of it, really recognize and acknowledge what it is doing.

135
00:26:36,779 --> 00:26:42,487
We're interested in the mood, emotion, mental state or attitude that is driving the fantasies.

136
00:26:44,769 --> 00:26:46,010
Let go of the story.

137
00:26:46,612 --> 00:26:50,537
We're only interested in what is actually motivating it.

138
00:26:51,357 --> 00:26:55,123
Irritation, irritation, excitement, excitement.

139
00:26:56,436 --> 00:27:24,874
then draw the attention back to the breath and determine to stay there feeling sleepy or tired keep making that effort lifting up opening the eyes and don't forget if the dullness and lethargy become overwhelming you can stand up allowing the attention to settle on the breath as we feel more settled

140
00:27:25,546 --> 00:27:36,864
Draw yourself closer to see if you can catch the very beginning of the in-breath, stay with it to the very end, and the very beginning of the out-breath, and stay with it to the very end.

141
00:27:38,747 --> 00:27:46,980
If when you do this you find yourself getting tense, then sit back within yourself and have the impression of receiving the breath.

142
00:27:50,200 --> 00:27:55,603
rising, rising, falling, falling.

143
00:30:40,282 --> 00:30:49,873
From now on, when the mind wanders and you recognize and acknowledge what's driving it, instead of coming back to the breath, come back into the body.

144
00:30:50,513 --> 00:30:51,654
See if you can feel it.

145
00:30:53,155 --> 00:30:57,201
If it is excitement, come into the body and see if you can feel the agitation.

146
00:30:58,801 --> 00:31:01,484
Feel the restlessness and perhaps heat of worry.

147
00:31:02,705 --> 00:31:05,229
If it's romance, feel the warmth and happiness.

148
00:31:07,070 --> 00:31:09,192
Stay there till it all evaporates.

149
00:31:10,996 --> 00:31:14,259
and again feeling dull-minded or lethargic in the body.

150
00:31:15,780 --> 00:31:19,984
You can also get into the feel of these states, the sensations, the feelings.

151
00:31:20,945 --> 00:31:25,190
Keep energising the spine, and you can still open the eyes to let the light in.

152
00:31:28,834 --> 00:31:31,896
When we get lost, we can always begin with the breath.

153
00:31:33,117 --> 00:31:35,519
The breath is our anchor and reference point.

154
00:31:37,001 --> 00:31:40,125
When we're confused, for instance, best to go back to the breath.

155
00:31:42,670 --> 00:31:44,454
Let's begin again with the breath.

156
00:31:46,038 --> 00:31:51,192
Rising, rising, falling, falling.

157
00:31:54,180 --> 00:31:58,771
And find the noting you need just to help keep the attention steady.

158
00:34:42,862 --> 00:34:47,507
becoming aware of how we are reacting to what we're experiencing.

159
00:34:48,869 --> 00:34:54,416
How when something is pleasant, we're drawn towards it, we want to maintain it, to develop it.

160
00:34:55,637 --> 00:34:57,739
Can you feel the force of that desire?

161
00:34:59,661 --> 00:35:05,068
When something is unpleasant, we first ignore it, but then we just want to get rid of it.

162
00:35:05,789 --> 00:35:09,134
If the posture is a little uncomfortable, we want to change it.

163
00:35:10,414 --> 00:35:12,818
Can you feel the strength of the desire?

164
00:35:13,422 --> 00:35:16,507
Can you feel these desires and not do anything?

165
00:35:17,688 --> 00:35:21,934
Just allow them to express themselves and exhaust themselves.

166
00:35:25,481 --> 00:35:32,592
This is the desire the Buddha points to as the psychological cause for our suffering and unsatisfactoriness.

167
00:35:34,835 --> 00:35:35,936
Is that true for you?

168
00:38:20,666 --> 00:38:26,195
becoming aware of how everything we are experiencing is arising and passing away.

169
00:38:27,818 --> 00:38:29,340
Everything is in a process.

170
00:38:29,940 --> 00:38:31,123
Nothing repeats itself.

171
00:38:32,324 --> 00:38:35,048
Even though each breath is similar, they're never the same.

172
00:38:36,572 --> 00:38:38,414
Everything is vanishing, disappearing.

173
00:38:39,416 --> 00:38:40,318
Nothing remains.

174
00:38:42,800 --> 00:38:44,463
Is there anything reliable?

175
00:41:28,586 --> 00:41:33,173
Becoming more aware of how everything we're experiencing is an object.

176
00:41:35,197 --> 00:41:41,065
If we have discomfort in the knee, we're looking down from the position in the forehead as the observer.

177
00:41:42,186 --> 00:41:44,128
It's a sort of observation post.

178
00:41:46,233 --> 00:41:54,864
Can we make that separation, that distance between the observer, the feeler, the experiencer and the object more obvious to us?

179
00:41:56,295 --> 00:42:02,364
At times we can use a word like there, so there's aching, there over there is an itch.

180
00:42:04,088 --> 00:42:09,577
If it's an emotion or mood in the body, there's irritation, there's excitement.

181
00:42:11,219 --> 00:42:16,447
When it is an image in the mind right in front of you, you can point to it, there's an image.

182
00:42:17,668 --> 00:42:20,092
You might even be able to do this with a thought.

183
00:42:22,402 --> 00:42:31,679
Are the observer and the observed, the feeler and the felt, the experiencer and the experienced, the same or distinct?

184
00:42:34,987 --> 00:42:37,592
Can the perceiver be the perceived?

185
00:43:38,896 --> 00:43:39,422
Thank you.

186
00:45:22,643 --> 00:45:27,449
becoming more aware of how everything is happening of its own accord.

187
00:45:29,271 --> 00:45:35,237
In Avipassana, we've taken the objective position of the observer, the feeler, the experiencer.

188
00:45:35,777 --> 00:45:42,106
We've separated out from the psychophysical organism and allowed it to manifest as it wants.

189
00:45:43,708 --> 00:45:51,536
We find that the body offers us sensations and feelings, pleasant and unpleasant, whether we want it to or not.

190
00:45:53,052 --> 00:46:07,704
the heart, its moods and emotions, pleasant and unpleasant, whether we want it to or not, and the mind, its thoughts and images, wholesome and unwholesome, whether we want it to or not.

191
00:46:09,365 --> 00:46:11,226
We don't have direct control.

192
00:46:14,130 --> 00:46:22,637
If control is being exercised by the body, the heart and the mind, how can they be me

193
00:49:07,974 --> 00:49:21,891
Putting aside all instruction, have absolute confidence that this intuitive awareness is able to understand the way things really are, that it can have profound insight into the nature of things.

194
00:49:22,753 --> 00:49:25,675
We don't need to keep thinking about it, prompting it.

195
00:49:26,456 --> 00:49:27,719
No need to do anything.

196
00:49:28,519 --> 00:49:30,141
Don't try and change anything.

197
00:49:31,182 --> 00:49:35,467
Just absolute acceptance of this is the way it is.

198
00:49:36,376 --> 00:49:45,998
All we need to do is just observe, just feel, just experience whatever draws the attention within the field of awareness.

199
00:52:30,559 --> 00:52:36,864
When we come to the end of a sitting, it's good to spend a little time reflecting on our experience.

200
00:52:37,985 --> 00:52:40,708
You can ask questions of yourself.

201
00:52:40,728 --> 00:52:44,492
How diligent was I in bringing myself back to the present moment?

202
00:52:55,742 --> 00:52:59,605
If I thought I was diligent, then I should congratulate myself.

203
00:53:00,579 --> 00:53:06,045
If I thought I could have been a little more committed, I should encourage myself.

204
00:53:06,507 --> 00:53:08,869
There's no need for self-criticism.

205
00:53:19,601 --> 00:53:23,505
Was there some mental state or physical state that you had to work with?

206
00:53:24,007 --> 00:53:26,849
Some form of discomfort or agitation, perhaps?

207
00:53:28,532 --> 00:53:29,693
Some sleepiness?

208
00:53:30,853 --> 00:53:31,954
How did you deal with it?

209
00:53:32,775 --> 00:53:33,936
Just choose one of them.

210
00:53:47,608 --> 00:53:51,233
If you thought you were skillful, you can congratulate yourself.

211
00:53:52,833 --> 00:53:57,659
If you thought you could have been a little more committed, you could encourage yourself.

212
00:53:58,079 --> 00:54:00,320
Don't get into self-criticism.

213
00:54:13,159 --> 00:54:15,784
In this sitting, what was most prominent for you?

214
00:54:16,125 --> 00:54:19,851
The role of desire in creating unsatisfactoriness?

215
00:54:21,195 --> 00:54:22,998
Or was it the impermanence of things?

216
00:54:24,420 --> 00:54:30,612
Or was it that everything you were experiencing was an object, not under your direct control?

217
00:54:43,552 --> 00:54:45,173
And it's good to make a resolution.

218
00:54:46,034 --> 00:54:47,376
It can be quite specific.

219
00:54:48,396 --> 00:54:51,619
Next time I feel dozy, I'll immediately open my eyes.

220
00:54:53,001 --> 00:54:56,704
Or it can be a general commitment to affectionate mindfulness.

221
00:55:07,554 --> 00:55:10,237
When we come out of a sitting, don't jump out of it.

222
00:55:11,398 --> 00:55:12,900
Open the eyes gently.

223
00:55:13,521 --> 00:55:14,655
and let the light in.

